UserComments: [{'ID': 21784, 'ChargePointID': 112691, 'CommentTypeID': 10, 'CommentType': {'ID': 10, 'Title': 'General Comment'}, 'UserName': 'TeslaFRA', 'Comment': 'Had been charging successfully and there are people looking for the little information booth to the left on the picture. Nothing then nature around, so be prepared and if you park there, take some trash with you, if you see some. There are no trash bins ! Just nature. A very quiet spot. Every 3-5 minutes a car was passing by. You could here a car two minutes before it was actually passing. Something very unusual for me as a city person. The little house is housing an online information with internet access, which did not really work or I was to stupid to use it. There is a lake and two benches. No table and no toilet.
